snippet.textDisplay:
QUESTION: WHERE THE HELL IS KOBE'S HELICOPTER, SERIOUSLY? Follow closely sports fans:

Fact 1) As we know, NO two aircraft have the same Tail, or N-Number.

Fact 2) As we know, the "confirmed" tail number of the helicopter that Kobe and 8 others crashed in was reportedly Kobe's private Sikorsky S-76B with the tail number of N72EX.

Fact 3) NTSB database does not indicate any other accidents associated with the same tail number. According to the FAA registration database, the vehicle was previously owned by the state of Illinois was owned by a company named Island Express Holding Corp. and had previously belonged to the state of Illinois.

Fact 4) Island Express Holding Corp. of Van Nuys bought the helicopter and changed its tail number to N72EX -- the identifier IT WAS USING WHEN IT WENT DOWN SUNDAY. As reported, "The helicopter that crashed Sunday is the same craft Bryant took to his final game in April 2016", a full year after being custom painted...

STILL WITH ME HERE?

Fact 5) An online database indicates the tail number was changed to N72EX in 2015 when it was purchased by the Island Express Holding Corporation of Van Nuys, California, the holding company of record at the time of the crash. Flight tracking websites show the helicopter which originally was painted WHITE with TWO-TONE BLUE STRIPES, received a NEW PAINT-JOB, including the Nike swoosh logo and Kobe Bryant’s signature “sheath” insignia (as pictured) after the 2015 ownership change. THAT WAS 5-YEARS AGO...

STILL FOLLOWING CAMPERS?

Fact 6) As we know, Kobe's DARK-GRAY helicopter, tail number N72EX is CLEARLY NOT, NOT, NOT the aircraft pictured in the news of the crash site yesterday.
Tail numbers DON'T LIE.

Fact 7) However, as we now know, SOMEONE HERE IS LYING!

Fact 😎 I share here ample photo documentation of each to back up my case. But then, what do I know, I'm just a curious, detail minded internationally awarded aviation artist...

SO --- MY QUESTION STILL REMAINS: Where in the hell is Kobe's helicopter,,, ANYONE?
